You're Director Oh's secretary,
right?

5
00:01:14,780 --> 00:01:16,490
What size are you?
We're wearing the same shoes.

6
00:01:25,207 --> 00:01:27,751
HAEMU GROUP
2022 REGULAR BOARD MEETING

7
00:01:30,796 --> 00:01:32,506
The human heart

8
00:01:33,549 --> 00:01:34,883
can be so fickle.

9
00:01:36,594 --> 00:01:38,345
I really was grateful.

10
00:01:52,943 --> 00:01:54,695
But the fact that hers was
a designer brand

11
00:01:55,487 --> 00:01:57,740
and mine were cheap knockoffs

12
00:01:58,907 --> 00:02:01,410
made me feel conflicted.

13
00:02:13,172 --> 00:02:15,299
- Hello.
- Yes, hello.

14
00:02:15,382 --> 00:02:18,260
Is Ms. Joo In-a not in today?

15
00:02:18,510 --> 00:02:19,803
She was transferred abroad.

16
00:02:20,095 --> 00:02:21,847
She won't be back for a while.

17
00:02:28,562 --> 00:02:31,148
She had taken one of my knockoffs.

18
00:02:32,775 --> 00:02:34,360
I wonder how she felt about it.

19
00:02:35,486 --> 00:02:37,571
This request is from Finance.

20
00:02:37,655 --> 00:02:39,573
They are customary expenses.

21
00:02:39,657 --> 00:02:41,700
You only need to take a brief look
before you approve it.

22
00:02:41,784 --> 00:02:42,868
I'll read it through.

23
00:02:43,202 --> 00:02:44,745
Not all customs are appropriate.

24
00:02:46,288 --> 00:02:47,289
Right.

25
00:02:49,583 --> 00:02:51,085
You can sign the form with this...

26
00:03:07,017 --> 00:03:08,227
Your shoes are nice.

27
00:03:09,937 --> 00:03:10,938
Pardon?

28
00:03:14,149 --> 00:03:15,192
Never mind.

29
00:03:15,901 --> 00:03:16,985
If only

30
00:03:17,903 --> 00:03:20,072
I had known then what that meant

31
00:03:20,698 --> 00:03:22,825
I wouldn't have fallen for him.

32
00:03:26,620 --> 00:03:29,415
They say great love
is akin to deep resentment.

33
00:03:29,498 --> 00:03:30,833
REPORTING MS. JOO IN-A

34
00:03:31,542 --> 00:03:33,585
Do I love Jeon Jae-yeol?

35
00:03:33,669 --> 00:03:34,837
...AND HER SUPERIOR, WHO IS MARRIED

36
00:03:34,920 --> 00:03:36,630
Or do I resent Joo In-a?

37
00:03:44,680 --> 00:03:45,764
SEND

38
00:03:46,390 --> 00:03:48,809
EMAIL WAS SENT SUCCESSFULLY

39
00:03:52,062 --> 00:03:55,816
EPISODE 10:
IRREVERSIBLE

40
00:03:56,650 --> 00:03:58,861
NEW MESSAGES

41
00:04:02,656 --> 00:04:03,824
NEW MESSAGES

42
00:04:03,907 --> 00:04:05,367
Is the rumor about Ms. Joo true?

43
00:04:05,451 --> 00:04:07,035
How's the atmosphere at work?

44
00:04:07,119 --> 00:04:08,871
Do you know anything about this?

45
00:04:45,073 --> 00:04:47,034
ARE YOU ALL RIGHT?

46
00:04:58,295 --> 00:04:59,421
Hello?

47
00:05:01,340 --> 00:05:02,341
Yes, sir.

48
00:05:05,928 --> 00:05:07,095
I understand.

49
00:05:12,768 --> 00:05:14,102
I'm all right

50
00:05:14,186 --> 00:05:15,938
but I don't think my higher-ups are.

51
00:05:18,398 --> 00:05:19,691
I have to go upstairs.

52
00:05:36,416 --> 00:05:39,753
Listen up. You must have
a lot to talk about.

53
00:05:40,587 --> 00:05:42,965
It must be frustrating
to keep sending messages.

54
00:05:43,799 --> 00:05:45,384
I'll be away for a meeting.

55
00:05:45,467 --> 00:05:50,430
Use your voice freely
and talk as much as you want.

56
00:05:51,306 --> 00:05:52,599
But once I return

57
00:05:53,600 --> 00:05:55,352
you must all focus on your tasks.

58
00:05:58,105 --> 00:05:59,106
Do you understand?

59
00:06:09,700 --> 00:06:11,869
J CONVALESCENT HOSPITAL

60
00:06:16,498 --> 00:06:17,875
Do you like this show that much?

61
00:06:21,837 --> 00:06:23,005
Your son is here.

62
00:06:23,088 --> 00:06:25,507
You've been staring
at the TV for hours.

63
00:06:51,158 --> 00:06:52,701
MISSED CALLS

64
00:06:52,784 --> 00:06:54,494
NEW MESSAGES

65
00:07:00,751 --> 00:07:02,210
REPORTING MS. JOO IN-A

66
00:07:02,294 --> 00:07:03,754
...AN INAPPROPRIATE
WORKPLACE RELATIONSHIP

67
00:07:07,382 --> 00:07:11,845
How could the audit head
find herself in such accusations?

68
00:07:11,929 --> 00:07:12,930
How are they accusations?

69
00:07:13,221 --> 00:07:15,098
They're just one-sided claims
by the email sender.

70
00:07:15,182 --> 00:07:17,351
But there's a photo for proof.

71
00:07:18,185 --> 00:07:19,853
What exactly is going on here?

72
00:07:20,938 --> 00:07:23,106
I'm greeting this person warmly.

73
00:07:23,815 --> 00:07:26,735
This isn't the US.
No one greets people like this here.

74
00:07:27,027 --> 00:07:30,614
Why would you say something
that awkward and old-fashioned?

75
00:07:31,114 --> 00:07:33,700
Let's forget all that
and cut to the chase.

76
00:07:34,117 --> 00:07:35,369
So who is it?

77
00:07:35,619 --> 00:07:38,246
Who's the man in the photo
that you exchanged greetings with?

78
00:07:50,884 --> 00:07:51,885
Jae-yeol.

79
00:08:00,143 --> 00:08:01,478
Long time no see.

80
00:08:01,979 --> 00:08:03,313
You're in my seat.

81
00:08:20,330 --> 00:08:22,874
Is this Ms. Joo's
disciplinary hearing or something?

82
00:08:23,667 --> 00:08:25,210
That's not it, sir.

83
00:08:25,293 --> 00:08:27,671
Then is the whole board
grilling an employee

84
00:08:27,754 --> 00:08:29,840
because of one spam email?

85
00:08:35,303 --> 00:08:36,471
Don't you have better things to do?

86
00:08:38,015 --> 00:08:40,183
This is more than enough cause
for an emergency meeting.

87
00:08:40,267 --> 00:08:42,477
The whole company's in uproar.

88
00:08:44,146 --> 00:08:46,898
We all got one malicious email
that doesn't even have much detail

89
00:08:47,232 --> 00:08:49,401
and the whole board convened
because of it.

90
00:08:50,027 --> 00:08:51,278
Isn't that ridiculous?

91
00:08:52,070 --> 00:08:53,697
This report isn't about just anyone.

92
00:08:53,780 --> 00:08:56,033
It's about our head of audit.

93
00:08:56,491 --> 00:09:00,662
Are you defending her because
you care about her more than average?

94
00:09:11,256 --> 00:09:13,258
Call the head of HR
to my office immediately.

95
00:09:18,138 --> 00:09:19,514
What impeccable timing.

96
00:09:20,182 --> 00:09:22,184
You refused to come in for days

97
00:09:22,267 --> 00:09:25,395
but then you show up as soon
as you hear Ms. Joo's in trouble.

98
00:09:28,356 --> 00:09:30,942
I'm saying
it's good to see you're back.

99
00:09:31,985 --> 00:09:33,695
I'll call HR right away.

100
00:09:38,033 --> 00:09:41,286
I believe the email was sent
to every employee's account.

101
00:09:41,912 --> 00:09:43,413
Search traffic for Ms. Joo

102
00:09:43,497 --> 00:09:46,416
as well as for most male executives
has increased significantly.

103
00:09:46,500 --> 00:09:49,294
I believe it's related
to this incident.

104
00:09:50,921 --> 00:09:52,047
Ms. Boo.

105
00:09:52,756 --> 00:09:55,675
Emails or posts like these
that comment on one's privacy...

106
00:09:55,884 --> 00:09:57,219
Yes, sir.

107
00:09:58,095 --> 00:10:01,348
It wouldn't be a problem
if the person followed protocol

108
00:10:01,431 --> 00:10:03,183
and contacted the Audit Team.

109
00:10:03,683 --> 00:10:06,186
But I believe widespread exposure

110
00:10:06,269 --> 00:10:08,522
such as this instance,
could carry legal repercussions.

111
00:10:09,356 --> 00:10:10,440
Am I right?

112
00:10:11,775 --> 00:10:13,360
Well, yes.

113
00:10:13,443 --> 00:10:17,989
The person emailed the whole company,
so whether it's true or not

114
00:10:18,281 --> 00:10:20,158
it could be grounds for defamation.

115
00:10:21,326 --> 00:10:24,162
If the email was sent
from the outside to all employees

116
00:10:24,830 --> 00:10:27,791
it means it's possible
the email list was leaked.

117
00:10:27,874 --> 00:10:31,628
For security purposes,
we should track the sender.

118
00:10:32,295 --> 00:10:35,006
Right. I'll get IT
and the Information Office

119
00:10:35,090 --> 00:10:36,383
to trace the sender's IP.

120
00:10:36,466 --> 00:10:38,343
Call me as soon as you get something.

121
00:10:38,426 --> 00:10:39,636
Yes, sir.

122
00:11:04,703 --> 00:11:06,538
Are you heading home, Ms. Joo?

123
00:11:11,501 --> 00:11:13,670
Is the food to your liking?

124
00:11:15,630 --> 00:11:16,882
Of course, it is.

125
00:11:17,048 --> 00:11:18,550
Rice is our staple food.

126
00:11:20,844 --> 00:11:22,012
You smile easily.

127
00:11:23,430 --> 00:11:25,932
So why are you so stiff
in that photo?

128
00:11:26,224 --> 00:11:28,101
You said it was a warm greeting.

129
00:11:29,853 --> 00:11:31,479
You shouldn't jump to conclusions

130
00:11:31,855 --> 00:11:33,857
based on a photo taken
in a split second.

131
00:11:35,817 --> 00:11:38,653
I can and will make
whatever conclusion I want.

132
00:11:38,737 --> 00:11:39,738
My status allows it.

133
00:11:42,407 --> 00:11:45,577
Whether this will end
as a random incident

134
00:11:46,578 --> 00:11:48,705
or turn into a scandal

135
00:11:49,039 --> 00:11:51,208
all depends on what you say next.

136
00:11:56,755 --> 00:11:59,591
I've been watching you, Ms. Joo.

137
00:12:00,217 --> 00:12:04,054
I noticed at the workshop
that you'll never side with me.

138
00:12:04,137 --> 00:12:06,681
But it doesn't look like
you're on Jae-yeol's side either.

139
00:12:08,266 --> 00:12:11,811
Don't you think it's time
to make your intentions clear?

140
00:12:17,359 --> 00:12:18,818
If I take this shot

141
00:12:19,110 --> 00:12:21,947
does that mean I vow
to be loyal to you or something?

142
00:12:23,031 --> 00:12:26,117
I'd love to have
a big sister like you.

143
00:12:29,913 --> 00:12:31,623
If you know I'm older

144
00:12:32,290 --> 00:12:34,334
then you shouldn't
threaten me like this.

145
00:12:36,962 --> 00:12:39,673
You took it as a threat.
That's a shame.

146
00:12:40,632 --> 00:12:42,050
I hoped you'd take it
as a suggestion.

147
00:12:42,884 --> 00:12:43,927
In that case...

148
00:12:45,971 --> 00:12:48,056
It's a suggestion I must pass on.

149
00:12:50,475 --> 00:12:52,936
What a pity. The drink looked tasty.

150
00:12:53,228 --> 00:12:54,271
Instead

151
00:12:54,813 --> 00:12:55,939
I'll pay for dinner.

152
00:13:10,453 --> 00:13:11,496
I see

153
00:13:12,831 --> 00:13:14,332
she doesn't take me seriously.

154
00:13:32,642 --> 00:13:35,854
HEAD OF AUDIT

155
00:13:35,937 --> 00:13:37,230
AUDIT TEAM HEAD JOO IN-A

156
00:13:37,314 --> 00:13:38,440
Can I help you?

157
00:13:39,149 --> 00:13:40,191
Excuse us, Ms. Joo.

158
00:13:44,988 --> 00:13:46,281
What do you think you're doing?

159
00:13:46,364 --> 00:13:48,366
You can't do this.
She's the Head of Audit.

160
00:13:49,993 --> 00:13:53,455
Company regulations say
this is my team's job.

161
00:13:53,872 --> 00:13:55,123
This is a refreshing turn of events.

162
00:13:55,832 --> 00:13:57,584
We have Vice President
Jeon Sung-yeol's order

163
00:13:57,834 --> 00:14:01,504
to thoroughly investigate
the email we received about you.

164
00:14:02,047 --> 00:14:05,175
As you are mentioned in the email

165
00:14:05,258 --> 00:14:08,011
VP Jeon Sung-yeol's office
will carry out the investigation.

166
00:14:22,650 --> 00:14:23,651
What?

167
00:14:27,864 --> 00:14:28,865
What's going on?

168
00:14:30,325 --> 00:14:33,453
I guess I fell victim
to company politics.

169
00:14:34,954 --> 00:14:36,956
VP Jeon Sung-yeol hates me.

170
00:14:37,290 --> 00:14:40,210
He said he won't let me off for this
unless I side with him.

171
00:14:41,294 --> 00:14:42,670
I said no, of course.

172
00:14:45,757 --> 00:14:47,675
Don't frown. You'll get wrinkles.

173
00:14:51,137 --> 00:14:53,181
You know this is all
about politics now, don't you?

174
00:14:53,848 --> 00:14:56,393
No amount of logic or fact will work.

175
00:14:56,976 --> 00:14:59,562
Clench your teeth and hang in there.
And when you think you can't...

176
00:15:00,730 --> 00:15:01,731
When you can't...

177
00:15:02,774 --> 00:15:03,775
Then...

178
00:15:05,568 --> 00:15:06,569
Then what?

179
00:15:09,030 --> 00:15:11,574
Are you going to save me
like a knight in shining armor?

180
00:15:12,409 --> 00:15:13,618
Shall I?

181
00:15:15,412 --> 00:15:16,830
I'm afraid you'll actually do that.

182
00:15:18,373 --> 00:15:21,584
Don't worry. My career spans years.

183
00:15:22,293 --> 00:15:23,878
If this is how he acts

184
00:15:24,504 --> 00:15:27,424
I should come up
with something more strategic.

185
00:15:28,758 --> 00:15:29,926
What kind of strategy?

186
00:15:31,177 --> 00:15:33,721
You said this is you
greeting someone.

187
00:15:34,389 --> 00:15:35,640
Yes, that is true.

188
00:15:37,934 --> 00:15:42,021
Take another good look
at the photo and tell me

189
00:15:42,564 --> 00:15:44,274
who that person is.

190
00:15:50,155 --> 00:15:51,906
Gosh. I can't say.

191
00:15:53,158 --> 00:15:54,701
Who was this?

192
00:15:54,784 --> 00:15:56,661
Are you saying
you can't remember who it is

193
00:15:57,120 --> 00:15:58,788
you greeted that warmly?

194
00:15:58,872 --> 00:16:00,457
It's not that I can't remember.

195
00:16:01,583 --> 00:16:04,377
I greet so many people
in this manner.

196
00:16:04,669 --> 00:16:06,463
I can't tell everyone apart.

197
00:16:07,338 --> 00:16:09,841
I had just returned
from a long stint abroad.

198
00:16:10,175 --> 00:16:12,719
I greeted everyone I met like this.

199
00:16:12,802 --> 00:16:14,804
It's like a western-style greeting.

200
00:16:15,346 --> 00:16:16,389
You must know

201
00:16:16,473 --> 00:16:18,516
this is how people
greet each other abroad.

202
00:16:18,600 --> 00:16:20,310
I got so used to that custom.

203
00:16:20,852 --> 00:16:23,188
It took me a while to rediscover
my Confucian roots.

204
00:16:26,733 --> 00:16:27,901
Ms. Joo.

205
00:16:28,401 --> 00:16:29,736
Do you think this is a joke?

206
00:16:32,447 --> 00:16:34,991
Mr. Kim Deok-chul.

207
00:16:35,617 --> 00:16:37,243
I applaud the attempt

208
00:16:37,327 --> 00:16:39,496
but if you want
to intimidate someone...

209
00:16:42,790 --> 00:16:44,751
It's all about the sound effects.

210
00:16:46,794 --> 00:16:48,087
Get it?

211
00:16:56,012 --> 00:16:58,556
Do you think she'll be okay?

212
00:16:59,933 --> 00:17:02,101
The guys from the VP's office
will be tough on her.

213
00:17:02,727 --> 00:17:04,979
She's nothing but ego.
I wonder how she's doing.

214
00:17:05,563 --> 00:17:09,150
Am I the only one
who can't accept this?

215
00:17:09,400 --> 00:17:11,236
I get that they work for the VP

216
00:17:11,319 --> 00:17:13,821
but was there ever a precedent
where they investigated someone?

217
00:17:13,905 --> 00:17:15,323
If an investigation's needed

218
00:17:15,406 --> 00:17:18,785
they should form a task force team
to carry it out properly.

219
00:17:19,202 --> 00:17:21,746
I know he's the vice president,
this feels way out of...

220
00:17:29,170 --> 00:17:30,922
He crossed the line

221
00:17:31,339 --> 00:17:32,340
a lot.

222
00:17:32,423 --> 00:17:37,512
If levelheaded Mr. Noh is this upset
it means it's unreasonable.

223
00:17:37,887 --> 00:17:39,472
It is a bit weird.

224
00:17:40,056 --> 00:17:42,517
The email is pretty vague.

225
00:17:42,767 --> 00:17:46,104
It was a personal attack.
I don't see why it's such a big deal.

226
00:17:50,400 --> 00:17:51,442
So what?

227
00:17:52,443 --> 00:17:56,072
Will you all go over to complain
as you did for Mr. Moo?

228
00:17:56,155 --> 00:17:59,409
This isn't anything like that time.

229
00:17:59,492 --> 00:18:01,661
Anyone can tell this got political.

230
00:18:02,036 --> 00:18:04,247
Nothing we do will mean anything.

231
00:18:04,330 --> 00:18:06,291
We'll only get caught
in the crossfire.

232
00:18:06,374 --> 00:18:07,375
Still...

233
00:18:07,917 --> 00:18:10,420
not doing anything
makes me feel uncomfortable.

234
00:18:10,503 --> 00:18:12,338
Goodness.

235
00:18:12,422 --> 00:18:14,882
Do you think there's a way
to show how we feel?

236
00:18:14,966 --> 00:18:17,927
"We're behind you
and we support you."

237
00:18:18,011 --> 00:18:19,012
Something like that.

238
00:18:23,975 --> 00:18:25,977
I'll see you again tomorrow.

239
00:18:36,404 --> 00:18:38,114
Why are you all up here?

240
00:18:38,197 --> 00:18:40,116
Ms. Joo, aren't you hungry?

241
00:18:40,908 --> 00:18:43,828
Come with us.
Let's have a nice dinner.

242
00:18:50,126 --> 00:18:53,254
Hae-young was generous enough
to book a snow crab restaurant.

243
00:18:54,130 --> 00:18:57,342
These are nice and fleshy
because it's crab season.

244
00:18:57,425 --> 00:19:00,637
- Gosh, yes.
- Ms. Joo, this leg is packed.

245
00:19:00,720 --> 00:19:02,764
- Eat it up.
- No, the shell's better.

246
00:19:02,847 --> 00:19:04,766
Dip it in some ssamjang.

247
00:19:04,849 --> 00:19:06,476
- You need water.
- Ginger, too.

248
00:19:06,559 --> 00:19:08,811
- Where's the broth?
- Have some salad, too.

249
00:19:08,895 --> 00:19:10,355
What has gotten into you all?

250
00:19:11,481 --> 00:19:13,941
It feels like this is
my first birthday bash

251
00:19:14,025 --> 00:19:15,568
and I must put on a show for you.

252
00:19:15,652 --> 00:19:17,820
- Oh, gosh.
- That's not it.

253
00:19:18,196 --> 00:19:19,238
We're being silly.

254
00:19:20,531 --> 00:19:24,452
I know you organized this dinner
to cheer me up.

255
00:19:26,412 --> 00:19:27,747
I'm touched.

256
00:19:29,082 --> 00:19:30,083
Well...

257
00:19:30,792 --> 00:19:34,671
You're our fence and shelter
that keeps us safe.

258
00:19:35,088 --> 00:19:37,840
We need that fence and shelter
to stand tall to survive.

259
00:19:37,924 --> 00:19:40,718
I thought you weren't interested
in working at Haemu for much longer.

260
00:19:41,511 --> 00:19:43,763
He must want to stay for a long time
and embezzle as much as he can.

261
00:19:43,846 --> 00:19:45,515
Do you have to put it like that?

262
00:19:45,848 --> 00:19:46,974
It's not that.

263
00:19:47,266 --> 00:19:49,644
My kids are still young

264
00:19:49,727 --> 00:19:52,855
and I'm not sure if I ever can,
but I want to buy a house in Seoul.

265
00:19:53,523 --> 00:19:55,817
I put up with this kind of life
for a reason.

266
00:19:56,359 --> 00:19:57,735
My wife gives me

267
00:19:58,569 --> 00:19:59,946
just 200,000 won a month to spend.

268
00:20:00,029 --> 00:20:01,614
- Just 200,000 won?
- Yes.

269
00:20:02,031 --> 00:20:04,075
All breadwinner dads live like that.

270
00:20:04,492 --> 00:20:08,788
I plan to keep my job here
until my twins finish university.

271
00:20:08,871 --> 00:20:09,956
You should.

272
00:20:10,581 --> 00:20:13,292
Isn't it tough supporting
your boyfriend, Hae-young?

273
00:20:13,835 --> 00:20:16,003
No, well, it's not that bad.

274
00:20:16,087 --> 00:20:18,047
You're seeing someone?

275
00:20:18,131 --> 00:20:20,717
Yes, we've been dating for ten years.

276
00:20:20,800 --> 00:20:23,219
Are you still seeing that guy
who's into music?

277
00:20:23,302 --> 00:20:26,180
I told you to dump the guitarist
and find a golfer.

278
00:20:26,264 --> 00:20:28,641
Will you stop it?
I'd love to beat you up.

279
00:20:28,725 --> 00:20:30,143
You always do.

280
00:20:30,935 --> 00:20:32,270
What about you, Ms. Yoon?

281
00:20:32,645 --> 00:20:33,938
You're over-qualified and young, too.

282
00:20:34,021 --> 00:20:35,356
Don't you want a different job?

283
00:20:35,440 --> 00:20:36,524
No.

284
00:20:38,276 --> 00:20:41,070
I think all companies are the same.

285
00:20:43,156 --> 00:20:44,157
And...

286
00:20:44,741 --> 00:20:45,867
I like our team.

287
00:20:50,371 --> 00:20:51,748
What did you just say?

288
00:20:53,750 --> 00:20:55,001
I said, I like our team.

289
00:20:57,003 --> 00:21:00,131
My heart skipped a beat.
Was I the only one?

290
00:21:00,214 --> 00:21:02,967
Mine did, too. To hear that
from someone like Ms. Yoon...

291
00:21:03,050 --> 00:21:04,719
It's even more touching.

292
00:21:08,347 --> 00:21:09,348
Okay.

293
00:21:09,807 --> 00:21:11,893
With Team Three's love and support

294
00:21:12,143 --> 00:21:14,520
I promise to stay strong
for as long as I can.

295
00:21:14,937 --> 00:21:16,022
Thank you.

296
00:21:17,148 --> 00:21:18,775
You called me a fence and a shelter.

297
00:21:19,275 --> 00:21:21,778
No, a wall and an embankment.

298
00:21:22,153 --> 00:21:23,780
A fortress that circles a town.

299
00:21:23,863 --> 00:21:25,490
I'll be an iron fortress! Let's go!

300
00:21:25,573 --> 00:21:26,866
- Let's go!
- Let's go!

301
00:21:27,575 --> 00:21:29,368
- Cheers!
- Cheers!

302
00:21:29,452 --> 00:21:31,329
- Thank you!
- Thank you!

303
00:21:31,412 --> 00:21:32,580
How reassuring.

304
00:21:35,374 --> 00:21:37,543
- Gosh.
- Perfect.

305
00:21:38,002 --> 00:21:39,086
- Enjoy yourselves.
- Sure.

306
00:21:39,170 --> 00:21:40,338
Dig in.

307
00:21:48,179 --> 00:21:49,639
- It's good.
- Right?

308
00:21:49,722 --> 00:21:50,890
Hey.

309
00:21:51,808 --> 00:21:52,934
Not me.

310
00:21:53,935 --> 00:21:55,061
It looks great.

311
00:21:56,145 --> 00:21:59,148
There's a studio apartment
in Mr. Jeon's name

312
00:21:59,440 --> 00:22:01,234
but no one seems to live there

313
00:22:01,317 --> 00:22:03,236
and he doesn't seem
to go there often either.

314
00:22:03,319 --> 00:22:05,196
A studio apartment? Goodness.

315
00:22:05,279 --> 00:22:06,531
However

316
00:22:06,781 --> 00:22:09,075
he did visit this apartment complex
a few times.

317
00:22:09,867 --> 00:22:11,702
I checked who lives there.

318
00:22:15,665 --> 00:22:17,750
- She works at...
- I know who it is.

319
00:22:19,627 --> 00:22:20,795
Joo In-a.

320
00:22:23,756 --> 00:22:25,258
Why did he go see her?

321
00:22:26,008 --> 00:22:27,051
What are you doing?

322
00:22:28,219 --> 00:22:29,428
What's wrong?

323
00:22:30,179 --> 00:22:33,474
Who is Ji-a that you got her
a Serfe limited edition ring?

324
00:22:33,891 --> 00:22:35,768
And you even brought it
to our new home.

325
00:22:36,310 --> 00:22:37,854
Is she your darling love?

326
00:22:40,481 --> 00:22:41,858
Don't... Hang on.

327
00:23:24,734 --> 00:23:26,027
Wait.

328
00:23:27,320 --> 00:23:29,363
So JIA did not stand for Ji-a
but Joo In-a's initials.

329
00:23:30,907 --> 00:23:32,617
All this time.

330
00:23:36,621 --> 00:23:39,206
- Good job.
- Thank you, sir.

331
00:24:17,620 --> 00:24:18,663
Ms. Yoon.

332
00:24:19,163 --> 00:24:20,623
Do you have something to say to me?

333
00:24:27,380 --> 00:24:28,547
No.

334
00:24:33,219 --> 00:24:34,428
What was that?

335
00:24:39,725 --> 00:24:41,811
Hello, this is Noh Ki-jun
of Audit Team Three.

336
00:24:42,937 --> 00:24:45,231
What is it? What's the matter?

337
00:24:45,314 --> 00:24:46,357
Come over here.

338
00:24:47,733 --> 00:24:49,652
I shouldn't be telling you this

339
00:24:50,361 --> 00:24:52,697
but I came over
because it makes zero sense.

340
00:24:56,242 --> 00:24:57,952
You know, the email about Ms. Joo...

341
00:24:58,411 --> 00:25:00,496
My team tracked
the sender's IP address.

342
00:25:00,579 --> 00:25:03,207
So who does it belong to?
Who sent something like that?

343
00:25:04,792 --> 00:25:05,793
You did.

344
00:25:06,419 --> 00:25:08,921
- What?
- The sender's IP address

345
00:25:09,005 --> 00:25:10,965
was traced to your home, Ki-jun.

346
00:25:11,257 --> 00:25:12,883
I just can't believe it.

347
00:25:13,884 --> 00:25:16,971
Did you send it
because you hated her guts?

348
00:25:17,638 --> 00:25:19,473
For demoting you to handle PM cases?

349
00:25:21,642 --> 00:25:22,727
Hang on...

350
00:25:27,773 --> 00:25:29,066
The sender's location

351
00:25:29,608 --> 00:25:32,778
was traced to Mr. Noh Ki-jun's home.

352
00:25:42,621 --> 00:25:44,248
It's time to go, sir.

353
00:26:13,569 --> 00:26:17,031
NOH KI-JUN

354
00:26:26,540 --> 00:26:29,043
You have a lunch meeting
with Director Hwang

355
00:26:29,126 --> 00:26:31,128
before the conference
tomorrow afternoon.

356
00:26:31,212 --> 00:26:32,755
The traffic will be hectic.

357
00:26:33,798 --> 00:26:36,425
Shall I call the director
to change the restaurant?

358
00:26:41,555 --> 00:26:44,725
NOH KI-JUN

359
00:26:48,104 --> 00:26:49,105
Why don't you just take it?

360
00:26:50,564 --> 00:26:52,483
No, sir. It can wait.

361
00:26:54,527 --> 00:26:56,612
It looks like it's a call
you must take right now.

362
00:27:03,744 --> 00:27:05,412
Hi, what is it?

363
00:27:06,038 --> 00:27:07,748
Where are you? We need to talk.

364
00:27:08,207 --> 00:27:09,792
Not right now. Later on...

365
00:27:09,875 --> 00:27:11,043
Was it you?

366
00:27:11,752 --> 00:27:15,005
The email about Ms. Joo
was traced back to my home.

367
00:27:15,214 --> 00:27:16,215
Did you send it?

368
00:27:17,049 --> 00:27:19,093
The person
who sent the first email to me.

369
00:27:19,635 --> 00:27:20,636
That was you, wasn't it?

370
00:27:21,220 --> 00:27:22,888
Park A-jeong, why on earth did you...

371
00:27:22,972 --> 00:27:24,098
What were you think...

372
00:27:50,624 --> 00:27:51,667
Why did you do it?

373
00:27:52,376 --> 00:27:53,586
How did it look?

374
00:27:54,253 --> 00:27:55,796
You saw how you look together.

375
00:27:57,047 --> 00:27:59,383
Objectively speaking,
do you still think it's special?

376
00:28:00,384 --> 00:28:02,303
- What?
- I wanted you to see it.

377
00:28:02,720 --> 00:28:05,723
The love that you believe
is noble and special.

378
00:28:06,098 --> 00:28:09,977
It's no different from my feelings
that you disregard and dismiss.

379
00:28:10,060 --> 00:28:12,855
If you were angry with me,
you should've taken it out on me.

380
00:28:13,147 --> 00:28:15,816
- Why go after In-a...
- What is she to you?

381
00:28:16,984 --> 00:28:18,694
Don't you see me? I'm right here.

382
00:28:19,737 --> 00:28:22,114
Why does it have to be Joo In-a
and not me?

383
00:28:30,789 --> 00:28:32,458
I think this is it for us.

384
00:28:34,585 --> 00:28:35,711
Ms. Park.

385
00:28:36,629 --> 00:28:37,630
You're fired.

386
00:28:40,841 --> 00:28:43,636
Do I mean that little to you?

387
00:28:44,011 --> 00:28:45,471
Whatever you were,
you're not even that now.

388
00:28:49,058 --> 00:28:50,267
I'm sorry.

389
00:28:51,894 --> 00:28:53,437
It's me.

390
00:28:54,855 --> 00:28:57,691
I was the one
who always had eyes just for you.

391
00:28:57,942 --> 00:29:01,070
You pushed me away
like my feelings meant nothing.

392
00:29:01,153 --> 00:29:03,656
I just did it out of resentment.

393
00:29:05,324 --> 00:29:07,618
I know it was bad and wrong.

394
00:29:10,162 --> 00:29:12,373
Please don't abandon me.

395
00:29:43,946 --> 00:29:45,906
Good morning, Ms. Joo.

396
00:29:47,199 --> 00:29:49,576
What brings the busy vice president
who has no time to spare

397
00:29:49,660 --> 00:29:51,495
to come here in person?

398
00:29:56,000 --> 00:29:57,001
You're just as I thought.

399
00:29:57,626 --> 00:29:59,503
You're head of audit for a reason.

400
00:29:59,586 --> 00:30:02,089
My team couldn't get to you at all.

401
00:30:03,716 --> 00:30:04,800
Is that so?

402
00:30:06,051 --> 00:30:08,512
You seem to be
hanging in there pretty well.

403
00:30:09,179 --> 00:30:12,891
I know one trick I can use
to break people like you.

404
00:30:14,435 --> 00:30:15,519
It's finding your weakness.

405
00:30:17,396 --> 00:30:18,939
My weakness?

406
00:30:19,273 --> 00:30:21,734
I doubt you can find anything.

407
00:30:25,112 --> 00:30:28,115
You had a lovely dinner
after yesterday's interview

408
00:30:28,198 --> 00:30:29,408
with Team Three.

409
00:30:30,159 --> 00:30:31,243
What did you eat?

410
00:30:31,952 --> 00:30:34,621
Barbecue is boring, isn't it?

411
00:30:38,042 --> 00:30:39,668
What is your point exactly?

412
00:30:40,127 --> 00:30:43,380
I was told you
and Team Three had a great time.

413
00:30:43,464 --> 00:30:47,634
I wanted to know more about them,
so I read their personnel files.

414
00:30:50,763 --> 00:30:51,805
They're a mess.

415
00:30:53,515 --> 00:30:56,602
It's a miracle
Mr. Moo still has his job.

416
00:30:56,685 --> 00:30:59,355
And it's pure luck
that Mr. Cha was never penalized.

417
00:30:59,855 --> 00:31:02,149
Ms. Yoon's peers say
she's dreadful to work with.

418
00:31:04,026 --> 00:31:05,694
I'm thinking of calling HR

419
00:31:06,236 --> 00:31:09,531
to sort out Audit Team Three.

420
00:31:17,873 --> 00:31:18,874
How's that?

421
00:31:19,833 --> 00:31:21,001
Didn't I do pretty well

422
00:31:21,752 --> 00:31:22,753
in finding your weakness?

423
00:31:49,905 --> 00:31:51,824
You haven't changed,
leaving whenever you face trouble.

424
00:31:52,908 --> 00:31:55,577
It's now weird for us
to live under the same roof.

425
00:31:58,163 --> 00:31:59,248
Hey.

426
00:32:01,625 --> 00:32:03,377
I let you in because it was you

427
00:32:03,460 --> 00:32:05,379
when you suddenly barged in,
saying you had nowhere to go.

428
00:32:06,088 --> 00:32:09,842
For someone like you, who's so proud
and hates showing weakness

429
00:32:10,384 --> 00:32:12,886
I figured you must've had a reason
to come to me.

430
00:32:13,387 --> 00:32:15,722
That was why I let you in
without asking you anything.

431
00:32:17,099 --> 00:32:18,183
But...

432
00:32:21,395 --> 00:32:23,730
is this why you came to my house
in the first place?

433
00:32:23,814 --> 00:32:25,607
It's true I didn't have
anywhere else to go.

434
00:32:28,694 --> 00:32:30,320
And yes, there was a bit of a plan.

435
00:32:39,413 --> 00:32:40,747
This situation

436
00:32:41,373 --> 00:32:43,584
isn't advantageous
for Mr. Jeon Jae-yeol either.

437
00:32:44,251 --> 00:32:46,253
You said he was someone you loved.

438
00:32:46,545 --> 00:32:48,046
How can you do this if you love him?

439
00:32:48,130 --> 00:32:51,216
What you call love must be different
from what I call love.

440
00:32:51,300 --> 00:32:53,051
I can do even worse things!

441
00:33:00,476 --> 00:33:02,186
Thanks for everything.

442
00:33:03,061 --> 00:33:04,104
Take care.

443
00:33:28,587 --> 00:33:31,256
JOO IN-A

444
00:33:45,270 --> 00:33:47,272
Ms. Joo.

445
00:33:54,738 --> 00:33:55,906
Mr. Noh.

446
00:33:56,281 --> 00:33:57,324
Hey.

447
00:33:57,741 --> 00:33:58,825
Are you all right?

448
00:34:12,965 --> 00:34:14,341
Aren't I heavy?

449
00:34:16,426 --> 00:34:17,636
So light.

450
00:34:18,095 --> 00:34:19,763
You feel way too light.

451
00:34:21,557 --> 00:34:22,933
No, I'm heavy.

452
00:34:24,434 --> 00:34:26,103
Do you hate me because I'm so heavy?

453
00:34:27,604 --> 00:34:29,481
You really aren't heavy.

454
00:34:30,274 --> 00:34:32,109
But I'll hate you
if you drink this much.

455
00:34:35,320 --> 00:34:36,905
Don't hate me.

456
00:34:43,036 --> 00:34:45,747
Mr. Cha has to buy a home.

457
00:34:47,082 --> 00:34:50,460
Mr. Moo's kids
have to go to college, too.

458
00:34:51,753 --> 00:34:55,299
And Ms. Pyun needs
to marry her boyfriend.

459
00:34:58,844 --> 00:35:00,137
Are you crying?

460
00:35:00,929 --> 00:35:02,681
What? No.

461
00:35:08,312 --> 00:35:09,479
By any chance

462
00:35:10,897 --> 00:35:14,860
did Vice President Jeon Sung-yeol
blackmail you using our team?

463
00:35:17,446 --> 00:35:18,614
I don't think

464
00:35:20,657 --> 00:35:22,451
Far from being an iron fortress

465
00:35:25,746 --> 00:35:28,206
I feel like
I've become a rotting fence.

466
00:36:16,630 --> 00:36:17,881
This is Noh Ki-jun calling.

467
00:36:18,423 --> 00:36:19,591
May I see you for a moment?

468
00:36:44,157 --> 00:36:45,617
Would you like a drink?

469
00:36:45,826 --> 00:36:47,953
No, I drove here.

470
00:36:57,546 --> 00:36:58,714
Is In-a

471
00:37:00,048 --> 00:37:01,091
all right?

472
00:37:01,550 --> 00:37:02,968
If you're that worried

473
00:37:04,469 --> 00:37:06,054
it'd be more productive
for you to think of a way

474
00:37:06,138 --> 00:37:08,098
to patch up this incident.

475
00:37:11,560 --> 00:37:15,522
I heard the company tracked
the sender's IP to my house.

476
00:37:15,605 --> 00:37:17,566
I know it wasn't you.

477
00:37:18,525 --> 00:37:19,818
Just say I did it.

478
00:37:25,031 --> 00:37:27,617
I'll go to the disciplinary committee
and state I held a grudge against her

479
00:37:28,034 --> 00:37:29,911
for demoting me to the PM job
and tried to slander her.

480
00:37:29,995 --> 00:37:31,163
You cannot do that.

481
00:37:31,496 --> 00:37:32,914
Then do we tell the truth?

482
00:37:33,790 --> 00:37:35,167
Do we say that it was A-jeong?

483
00:37:35,959 --> 00:37:37,669
That'll expose her feelings for you

484
00:37:38,170 --> 00:37:39,921
and your relationship with Ms. Joo.

485
00:37:41,590 --> 00:37:42,591
They will all get exposed.

486
00:37:42,674 --> 00:37:44,342
Even so, that's still wrong.

487
00:37:45,385 --> 00:37:46,595
I'll pretend like I didn't hear it.

488
00:37:51,725 --> 00:37:52,809
Mr. Vice President.

489
00:37:57,147 --> 00:37:58,899
I'm doing this all for Ms. Joo.

490
00:38:05,530 --> 00:38:07,449
Then you will face
a disciplinary hearing, Mr. Noh.

491
00:38:08,575 --> 00:38:09,576
I don't care.

492
00:38:11,203 --> 00:38:14,247
It'll be much lighter
than the humiliation and dishonor

493
00:38:14,831 --> 00:38:16,291
she'll have to face
if I don't do this.

494
00:38:17,751 --> 00:38:18,752
On top of that

495
00:38:20,295 --> 00:38:22,964
I've never liked this company
even close to how much I like her.

496
00:38:52,828 --> 00:38:53,829
Yes, Se-young.

497
00:38:53,912 --> 00:38:55,497
Hey, you know
the disciplinary committee

498
00:38:55,580 --> 00:38:57,040
will be held at three o'clock, right?

499
00:38:57,749 --> 00:38:58,750
Yes.

500
00:38:59,251 --> 00:39:01,461
We'll have a testifier
make a statement first

501
00:39:02,087 --> 00:39:03,672
so come until four o'clock.

502
00:39:04,089 --> 00:39:05,298
A testifier?

503
00:39:06,758 --> 00:39:08,718
Who's the testifier
that's making a statement?

504
00:39:11,096 --> 00:39:14,307
The email sender decided to admit
that it was false information.

505
00:39:16,351 --> 00:39:17,435
Who's the sender?

506
00:39:18,186 --> 00:39:19,980
NOH KI-JUN

507
00:39:21,231 --> 00:39:24,317
The device is powered off.
You will be redirected to voicemail.

508
00:39:24,401 --> 00:39:25,402
After the beep...

509
00:39:31,491 --> 00:39:32,784
This is for the best.

510
00:39:33,577 --> 00:39:34,953
So please just make an order

511
00:39:35,537 --> 00:39:38,206
and have the disciplinary committee
summon me.

512
00:39:44,379 --> 00:39:46,006
Did you wish to see me,
Mr. Vice President?

513
00:39:46,089 --> 00:39:48,466
Ms. Joo's disciplinary committee
will be held today, correct?

514
00:39:49,050 --> 00:39:51,261
Yes, it's about to begin.

515
00:39:52,345 --> 00:39:54,598
There's no need
for you to be there yourself...

516
00:39:54,681 --> 00:39:55,682
No.

517
00:39:57,893 --> 00:39:59,019
I'll be there, too.

518
00:40:02,147 --> 00:40:06,401
Let us begin the disciplinary hearing
for Joo In-a, Head of Audit.

519
00:40:07,235 --> 00:40:10,906
The committee is here to deliberate
whether she violated

520
00:40:10,989 --> 00:40:13,950
the company regulations through
inappropriate personal conduct.

521
00:40:14,701 --> 00:40:16,620
Before we hear from Ms. Joo In-a

522
00:40:16,703 --> 00:40:20,123
we will hear from a testifier,
Mr. Noh Ki-jun

523
00:40:20,206 --> 00:40:22,500
regarding the email in question.

524
00:40:23,460 --> 00:40:25,086
I haven't heard about this.

525
00:40:25,629 --> 00:40:27,005
Why is Mr. Noh here?

526
00:40:27,088 --> 00:40:29,966
I apologize for not announcing
this matter beforehand.

527
00:40:30,467 --> 00:40:35,430
The IT Team in HR
tracked the sender's IP address.

528
00:40:36,389 --> 00:40:40,477
As a result, the one who sent
the email regarding Ms. Joo was...

529
00:40:48,652 --> 00:40:52,489
Ms. Joo, I thought I had notified you
to be here at 4 p.m.

530
00:40:53,865 --> 00:40:55,200
I'll take responsibility.

531
00:41:04,376 --> 00:41:06,252
I will take the responsibility
for everything...

532
00:41:06,336 --> 00:41:07,379
It was me.

533
00:41:14,719 --> 00:41:17,347
The man in the picture is me.

534
00:41:22,686 --> 00:41:24,020
Are you serious?

535
00:41:25,855 --> 00:41:27,273
What's going on between you two?

536
00:41:27,357 --> 00:41:30,235
Ms. Joo and I had dated in the past.

537
00:41:31,611 --> 00:41:33,363
However, after we separated
and I got married

538
00:41:33,571 --> 00:41:36,366
we have never been
in an inappropriate relationship.

539
00:41:38,910 --> 00:41:40,120
Then what were you doing there?

540
00:41:40,912 --> 00:41:42,122
Can you explain that?

541
00:41:49,254 --> 00:41:51,047
It was entirely my doing.

542
00:41:54,384 --> 00:41:55,927
I saw her
for the first time in a while

543
00:41:56,720 --> 00:41:57,887
and I faced emotions

544
00:41:58,888 --> 00:42:00,890
I didn't think
I still had left inside.

545
00:42:01,266 --> 00:42:02,434
So I made the mistake.

546
00:42:04,686 --> 00:42:05,895
She's actually the victim here.

547
00:42:08,106 --> 00:42:09,357
Ms. Joo

548
00:42:10,233 --> 00:42:13,653
did not do anything inappropriate.

549
00:42:29,419 --> 00:42:31,212
- It was the vice president.
- No way.

550
00:42:31,296 --> 00:42:33,298
- Seriously?
- What's going on, then?

551
00:42:35,717 --> 00:42:36,926
I can't believe this.

552
00:42:37,510 --> 00:42:38,720
I'm getting a headache right now.

553
00:42:39,012 --> 00:42:41,598
Ms. Joo truly is on another level.

554
00:42:41,681 --> 00:42:42,682
I mean, the vice president?

555
00:42:42,766 --> 00:42:44,934
But he said it wasn't
an inappropriate relationship.

556
00:42:45,018 --> 00:42:47,228
He also said
he had unresolved feelings.

557
00:42:47,854 --> 00:42:48,938
Isn't that considered cheating?

558
00:42:49,022 --> 00:42:50,940
How is that considered an affair?

559
00:42:51,024 --> 00:42:53,026
Emotional cheating
is also a form of an affair.

560
00:42:53,401 --> 00:42:56,529
If my boyfriend says
he's still hung up on his ex

561
00:42:56,613 --> 00:42:57,864
I'd break up with him then and there.

562
00:42:57,947 --> 00:42:59,783
But there were no actions taken.

563
00:42:59,866 --> 00:43:01,284
You can't really call it an affair.

564
00:43:01,367 --> 00:43:03,328
He did take action through a hug.

565
00:43:03,995 --> 00:43:06,039
Also, it was caught on camera.

566
00:43:06,122 --> 00:43:07,999
- Who knows what else they did?
- They didn't!

567
00:43:11,002 --> 00:43:13,671
I mean, why are you two still here?

568
00:43:14,005 --> 00:43:16,216
Why are you always chatting
in our area?

569
00:43:16,299 --> 00:43:18,093
If you want to do that,
volunteer to transfer here.

570
00:43:18,176 --> 00:43:19,427
You're here all the time

571
00:43:19,511 --> 00:43:21,971
so I'm not even sure whether
you two are on my team or not.

572
00:43:24,641 --> 00:43:26,559
The Audit Team... Gosh.

573
00:43:31,272 --> 00:43:32,315
Gosh.

574
00:43:33,024 --> 00:43:34,192
The vice president

575
00:43:34,901 --> 00:43:36,528
got to play the cool part all alone.

576
00:43:39,614 --> 00:43:41,783
Were you trying to be cool
by faking your statement?

577
00:43:43,409 --> 00:43:44,536
I heard everything.

578
00:43:44,869 --> 00:43:46,287
That you were planning to say

579
00:43:46,371 --> 00:43:49,082
that you sent
the wicked email out of spite.

580
00:43:49,582 --> 00:43:51,709
I thought that was the best
I could do in this situation.

581
00:43:52,418 --> 00:43:55,171
You were getting threatened
with that kind of nonsense

582
00:43:55,672 --> 00:43:57,173
so it was hard
to watch and do nothing.

583
00:43:57,465 --> 00:43:59,843
Did you think I'd sit and watch
if you said

584
00:44:00,718 --> 00:44:02,971
that you did something you didn't
because of me?

585
00:44:04,556 --> 00:44:06,432
This was the only thing I could do.

586
00:44:06,891 --> 00:44:09,978
I wanted to go this far
to protect you.

587
00:44:18,111 --> 00:44:19,821
I should stop getting in trouble.

588
00:44:20,405 --> 00:44:22,157
I might end up causing you trouble.

589
00:44:24,993 --> 00:44:25,994
Why?

590
00:44:26,202 --> 00:44:28,121
I liked how you called for me
when you were in trouble.

591
00:44:28,204 --> 00:44:29,622
You didn't even hesitate
to get on my back.

592
00:44:38,798 --> 00:44:40,717
- What is it?
- Give me a second.

593
00:44:41,176 --> 00:44:43,219
- Where are you going?
- Don't follow me.

594
00:44:51,895 --> 00:44:54,230
A-jeong, what's going on?

595
00:44:54,314 --> 00:44:55,565
Are you really quitting?

596
00:44:56,524 --> 00:44:58,401
It's so sudden.

597
00:44:59,444 --> 00:45:02,155
What am I going to do all alone
without you?

598
00:45:05,366 --> 00:45:06,618
Bye.

599
00:45:13,666 --> 00:45:14,709
A-jeong...

600
00:45:43,655 --> 00:45:45,156
So you do know what you did

601
00:45:45,907 --> 00:45:47,325
was worth a good slap.

602
00:45:52,330 --> 00:45:53,414
Why did you do that?

603
00:45:55,792 --> 00:45:57,210
It was an eyesore.

604
00:45:58,127 --> 00:45:59,212
All of you.

605
00:46:01,965 --> 00:46:03,007
Very explicit.

606
00:46:04,175 --> 00:46:06,636
So are you pleased
with this situation?

607
00:46:06,719 --> 00:46:07,929
I don't regret it.

608
00:46:08,513 --> 00:46:12,016
That precious love of yours
is now in shreds.

609
00:46:16,771 --> 00:46:18,273
But you're in shreds, too.

610
00:46:20,441 --> 00:46:21,651
Open your eyes

611
00:46:22,694 --> 00:46:24,320
and see who is falling apart.

612
00:46:32,287 --> 00:46:33,955
Are you out of your mind?

613
00:46:34,706 --> 00:46:36,124
Why did you step in?

614
00:46:37,166 --> 00:46:38,918
I'm doing my best to stop the news.
Don't worry.

615
00:46:39,002 --> 00:46:40,086
Keep your mouth shut!

616
00:46:40,837 --> 00:46:42,463
What do you think
your in-laws are going to do?

617
00:46:43,047 --> 00:46:44,841
What if they demand a divorce?

618
00:46:46,592 --> 00:46:47,802
Actually

619
00:46:48,886 --> 00:46:50,430
I had something to tell you.

620
00:46:52,056 --> 00:46:53,141
Who's there?

621
00:46:56,019 --> 00:46:57,270
It's me, Hyun-young.

622
00:46:58,521 --> 00:47:00,606
Hey, it's you, Hyun-young.

623
00:47:00,690 --> 00:47:02,025
Hello, Father.

624
00:47:02,400 --> 00:47:04,485
- Hyun-young.
- You were here, too.

625
00:47:08,406 --> 00:47:10,074
I heard everything out there.

626
00:47:10,616 --> 00:47:12,243
Are you furious, Father?

627
00:47:13,161 --> 00:47:16,080
You must be the one who's offended.

628
00:47:16,164 --> 00:47:18,416
My father has been
teaching him a lesson

629
00:47:18,499 --> 00:47:19,542
so don't be so harsh on him.

630
00:47:19,625 --> 00:47:21,252
No, I'm fine.

631
00:47:21,919 --> 00:47:23,671
I already knew

632
00:47:24,255 --> 00:47:25,923
about Ms. Joo and him.

633
00:47:26,883 --> 00:47:28,968
I told him to step up and be a man.

634
00:47:30,136 --> 00:47:32,597
It's so petty to stay quiet
while your ex-girlfriend

635
00:47:32,889 --> 00:47:34,057
is in trouble, don't you think?

636
00:47:36,726 --> 00:47:38,394
Look how chill she is about this.

637
00:47:38,478 --> 00:47:41,230
Jae-yeol, you have
one wonderful wife.

638
00:47:41,564 --> 00:47:42,815
Of course.

639
00:47:43,316 --> 00:47:44,692
I'm a member of the Sesan family.

640
00:47:49,906 --> 00:47:51,449
Anyway, that's that, Father.

641
00:47:52,658 --> 00:47:55,745
About the next development project
you're pushing with CPK.

642
00:47:56,371 --> 00:47:58,664
What do you think about Sesan
taking part in the consortium?

643
00:47:59,624 --> 00:48:00,958
Was that what you wanted to say?

644
00:48:01,918 --> 00:48:03,628
Is President Oh also aware?

645
00:48:04,045 --> 00:48:05,213
Of course.

646
00:48:05,296 --> 00:48:07,382
He wanted to make it extensive, too.

647
00:48:08,591 --> 00:48:10,843
Sesan's resources
and Haemu's technology

648
00:48:10,927 --> 00:48:13,763
should be enough to free the project
from CPK's influence.

649
00:48:13,846 --> 00:48:15,181
Yes, of course.

650
00:48:15,807 --> 00:48:17,517
All right. Then why don't we

651
00:48:18,142 --> 00:48:19,977
- set up a meeting with President Oh?
- But it does

652
00:48:20,603 --> 00:48:21,771
come with one condition.

653
00:48:29,362 --> 00:48:31,489
In the next general meeting

654
00:48:33,408 --> 00:48:34,450
appoint him publicly

655
00:48:35,576 --> 00:48:37,245
as the next president of the group.

656
00:48:38,996 --> 00:48:41,374
As President Jeon Jae-yeol.

657
00:48:59,016 --> 00:49:01,936
- What do you think you're doing?
- I'm trying to help you

658
00:49:02,186 --> 00:49:04,480
- and make you the successor.
- Yes, so why?

659
00:49:05,565 --> 00:49:07,483
- I told you already.
- That you want a divorce?

660
00:49:10,027 --> 00:49:11,279
Is that why

661
00:49:11,362 --> 00:49:13,614
you made that romantic announcement
in front of everyone?

662
00:49:15,241 --> 00:49:16,909
- That's...
- Freaking hilarious.

663
00:49:18,035 --> 00:49:19,287
One second.

664
00:49:20,455 --> 00:49:22,457
You gave me a dopamine rush.

665
00:49:24,292 --> 00:49:27,128
I couldn't believe you had
such romance in you, Jae-yeol.

666
00:49:28,838 --> 00:49:30,465
It's so intriguing.

667
00:49:32,133 --> 00:49:33,217
I...

668
00:49:34,760 --> 00:49:36,554
don't want to let you go anymore.

669
00:49:40,975 --> 00:49:42,268
Wait a second.

670
00:49:43,311 --> 00:49:44,687
Am I in love with Jeon Jae-yeol?

671
00:49:50,359 --> 00:49:51,819
- Hyun-young.
- Hubby.

672
00:49:54,113 --> 00:49:55,239
Dear husband!

673
00:49:55,823 --> 00:49:59,535
You can't afford
to defy me right now.

674
00:50:00,495 --> 00:50:03,372
I didn't just save you.

675
00:50:03,956 --> 00:50:05,458
I saved Joo In-a, too.

676
00:50:08,044 --> 00:50:09,587
You want to save her, don't you?

677
00:50:11,756 --> 00:50:12,798
That woman.

678
00:50:46,332 --> 00:50:48,209
Don't you think
our company is so much fun?

679
00:50:48,543 --> 00:50:50,962
The vice president himself
did an episode of EXchange for us.

680
00:50:52,129 --> 00:50:54,674
But talk
about Joo In-a's double standards.

681
00:50:54,757 --> 00:50:57,635
She's in the Audit Team
when she's dating the vice president.

682
00:50:57,718 --> 00:50:59,428
They aren't dating anymore.

683
00:50:59,887 --> 00:51:03,349
- They used to.
- You never know.

684
00:51:04,183 --> 00:51:07,144
Anyway, I've always been
suspicious of her.

685
00:51:07,436 --> 00:51:10,189
Her promotions came too early.
It must've been her looks.

686
00:51:11,107 --> 00:51:12,108
Oh, my.

687
00:51:12,858 --> 00:51:15,027
Is that supposed to be
a humiliation or a compliment?

688
00:51:15,111 --> 00:51:17,029
- Ms. Joo! I'm sorry.
- I'm sorry.

689
00:51:17,488 --> 00:51:18,739
I'm sorry.

690
00:51:18,823 --> 00:51:20,658
No, I was actually curious!

691
00:51:20,825 --> 00:51:23,160
What did you mean when you said
it must've been my looks?

692
00:51:24,078 --> 00:51:25,246
Ms. Joo.

693
00:51:25,871 --> 00:51:28,040
You don't have to mind them.
They aren't worth it.

694
00:51:30,334 --> 00:51:32,003
I'll buy you coffee.
Do you want an iced Americano?

695
00:51:32,086 --> 00:51:33,087
No.

696
00:51:33,462 --> 00:51:35,381
I'll buy my own strong coffee

697
00:51:35,464 --> 00:51:38,301
by adding two more shots
and down it quickly before I go up.

698
00:51:39,135 --> 00:51:40,970
You can go upstairs first, Mr. Noh.

699
00:51:51,939 --> 00:51:53,899
- Hello.
- Hey, Mr. Noh.

700
00:51:53,983 --> 00:51:54,984
You're here.

701
00:51:56,527 --> 00:51:59,405
What's so funny about all this?
They're all talking about Ms. Joo.

702
00:51:59,488 --> 00:52:00,781
Don't they have better things to do?

703
00:52:00,865 --> 00:52:02,408
Will she come to work today?

704
00:52:03,200 --> 00:52:04,619
I couldn't come if I were her.

705
00:52:04,702 --> 00:52:06,037
Why not?

706
00:52:06,120 --> 00:52:07,330
She was found innocent

707
00:52:07,413 --> 00:52:09,665
after the vice president
made that announcement.

708
00:52:09,749 --> 00:52:10,791
Exactly.

709
00:52:11,292 --> 00:52:13,377
It seemed like
he did that on purpose.

710
00:52:13,919 --> 00:52:15,004
It's kind of romantic.

711
00:52:16,005 --> 00:52:17,006
Romantic?

712
00:52:17,214 --> 00:52:20,259
Yesterday, you called it
emotional cheating and whatnot.

713
00:52:22,970 --> 00:52:23,971
What?

714
00:52:27,141 --> 00:52:28,351
Are you all right?

715
00:52:33,773 --> 00:52:34,774
Me?

716
00:52:40,780 --> 00:52:44,283
Hello, it's me, Joo In-a,
the talk of the town.

717
00:52:47,912 --> 00:52:49,455
I'm sure the mundane workplace

718
00:52:49,538 --> 00:52:51,248
must've been fun
for the last few days.

719
00:52:52,541 --> 00:52:54,251
All right, then.

720
00:52:54,669 --> 00:52:57,046
We're going back
to focused work mode.

721
00:52:57,546 --> 00:52:59,256
The general meeting is coming up.

722
00:52:59,924 --> 00:53:02,802
Mr. Ahn Min-su, I need the report
from the Audit Committee.

723
00:53:02,885 --> 00:53:03,886
Yes, ma'am.

724
00:53:17,191 --> 00:53:18,192
Father.

725
00:53:18,609 --> 00:53:20,319
You can't suddenly decide
on the successor

726
00:53:20,403 --> 00:53:22,446
because of Sesan's influence.

727
00:53:22,530 --> 00:53:24,240
Imagine how much Sesan will try
to control Haemu

728
00:53:24,323 --> 00:53:25,658
when Jae-yeol becomes the president.

729
00:53:25,741 --> 00:53:26,909
Be quiet!

730
00:53:27,159 --> 00:53:28,744
This is my decision to make.

731
00:53:29,495 --> 00:53:30,496
Father.

732
00:53:31,080 --> 00:53:34,291
His position at work isn't great
because of the scandal.

733
00:53:34,375 --> 00:53:36,127
It has hit rock bottom...

734
00:53:43,175 --> 00:53:46,971
VICE PRESIDENT JEON SUNG-YEOL

735
00:53:47,555 --> 00:53:50,474
Why?

736
00:53:51,308 --> 00:53:52,560
Damn it!

737
00:53:58,816 --> 00:53:59,900
Who's there?

738
00:54:03,070 --> 00:54:04,572
Should I come later?

739
00:54:05,906 --> 00:54:07,032
Hey, Doo-gi.

740
00:54:16,625 --> 00:54:20,546
It's about Haemu Pharmaceutical
you had mentioned before.

741
00:54:21,213 --> 00:54:24,550
During the forensics conducted on
Ms. Joo's computer for this incident

742
00:54:25,176 --> 00:54:27,511
the circumstances were spotted
that Haemu Pharmaceutical file

743
00:54:27,595 --> 00:54:29,263
was deleted on her computer.

744
00:54:30,014 --> 00:54:31,140
Ms. Joo?

745
00:54:31,223 --> 00:54:34,477
I'm not fully sure
what the file holds.

746
00:54:34,560 --> 00:54:37,438
But Vice President Jeon Jae-yeol
was a former president there

747
00:54:38,022 --> 00:54:42,443
and now we know he had a relationship
with Ms. Joo in the past.

748
00:54:43,778 --> 00:54:46,280
It didn't feel right
once I connected the dots.

749
00:55:05,007 --> 00:55:08,803
Jae-yeol must've held onto it,
no matter what it is.

750
00:55:11,472 --> 00:55:12,681
Is there anyone

751
00:55:13,641 --> 00:55:15,684
among his people
that we can win over?

752
00:55:20,105 --> 00:55:22,024
It's small but fully furnished

753
00:55:22,274 --> 00:55:23,943
so it's great if you wish
to move in right away.

754
00:55:24,026 --> 00:55:26,237
It won't be easy to find
a better place to rent.

755
00:55:30,866 --> 00:55:32,284
I'll take it.

756
00:55:33,786 --> 00:55:36,413
May I install
the double-latch myself?

757
00:55:36,497 --> 00:55:38,582
I'll let the landlord know
right away.

758
00:55:38,833 --> 00:55:40,668
Goodness, you're a young
and pretty lady

759
00:55:40,751 --> 00:55:42,962
so safety must be
your biggest concern.

760
00:55:43,420 --> 00:55:46,340
This neighborhood is quiet
and free from accidents.

761
00:55:47,007 --> 00:55:50,135
I see. I'll transfer
the holding deposit right now.

762
00:55:50,219 --> 00:55:51,428
Yes, sure.

763
00:55:57,768 --> 00:55:58,936
ACCOUNT HOLDER: PARK A-JEONG

764
00:55:59,019 --> 00:56:01,564
1,000,000 WON
NOT ENOUGH BALANCE

765
00:56:04,733 --> 00:56:07,444
- Your call cannot be connected.
- What did my brother do this time?

766
00:56:07,528 --> 00:56:09,280
Please leave a message
after the beep.

767
00:56:16,370 --> 00:56:17,413
Hello?

768
00:56:18,289 --> 00:56:20,457
- Is that you?
- Ms. Park?

769
00:56:28,215 --> 00:56:30,259
What do you want to say to me?

770
00:56:35,639 --> 00:56:36,807
Well...

771
00:56:37,516 --> 00:56:39,768
You knew about the relationship

772
00:56:40,561 --> 00:56:42,313
between my brother
and the Head of Audit, right?

773
00:56:44,064 --> 00:56:47,610
I mean, I could tell by the timing
that you must've been fired

774
00:56:48,027 --> 00:56:49,904
after calling him out frankly.

775
00:56:54,992 --> 00:56:57,786
That is not why I left.

776
00:56:58,078 --> 00:57:00,164
They weren't just dating.

777
00:57:00,789 --> 00:57:02,541
Their relationship affected
the company, too.

778
00:57:03,751 --> 00:57:04,793
Did you really not know?

779
00:57:05,210 --> 00:57:07,463
What do you mean?

780
00:57:07,546 --> 00:57:10,966
That is what I'm trying
to investigate in detail.

781
00:57:13,552 --> 00:57:14,678
May I

782
00:57:15,429 --> 00:57:17,890
ask for your help, Ms. Park?

783
00:57:23,479 --> 00:57:25,147
2025 HAEMU GROUP
GENERAL MEETING OF SHAREHOLDERS

784
00:57:25,230 --> 00:57:28,651
2025 HAEMU GROUP
GENERAL MEETING OF SHAREHOLDERS

785
00:57:59,682 --> 00:58:02,142
Why should we be
at the general meeting?

786
00:58:02,226 --> 00:58:05,354
Other companies make
their employees sit in, too. Come on.

787
00:58:05,437 --> 00:58:07,982
You probably didn't know
because you were in Audit Team One

788
00:58:08,065 --> 00:58:10,275
but Audit Team Three
always took part in these events

789
00:58:10,359 --> 00:58:11,902
when they required manpower.

790
00:58:11,986 --> 00:58:13,737
We were pretty much
Filler Team Three.

791
00:58:13,821 --> 00:58:14,989
- Come on.
- Let's go.

792
00:58:15,406 --> 00:58:18,325
That concludes this year's
financial audit report.

793
00:58:24,039 --> 00:58:27,418
There is a special agenda
scheduled for today's meeting.

794
00:58:27,501 --> 00:58:30,963
President Jeon Moo-tae will step up
and share it with us.

795
00:58:31,046 --> 00:58:32,673
Mr. President, please.

796
00:58:38,846 --> 00:58:41,890
I am aware of many different opinions
regarding personnel matters

797
00:58:41,974 --> 00:58:44,309
and management conditions.

798
00:58:46,395 --> 00:58:49,023
I am here today

799
00:58:49,106 --> 00:58:51,650
to share an important decision
regarding my position.

800
00:58:53,027 --> 00:58:54,903
I, Jeon Moo-tae

801
00:58:55,279 --> 00:58:56,613
will step down
as president as of today.

802
00:58:58,782 --> 00:59:00,409
Going forward

803
00:59:00,492 --> 00:59:03,162
Haemu Group will face
an even fiercer business climate.

804
00:59:04,246 --> 00:59:06,206
A leader for the group

805
00:59:06,290 --> 00:59:08,751
should be someone
with principle and decisiveness

806
00:59:09,168 --> 00:59:12,671
someone who can protect
the organization firmly.

807
00:59:13,756 --> 00:59:15,174
Hence, the board of directors

808
00:59:17,760 --> 00:59:19,053
has recommended

809
00:59:19,636 --> 00:59:22,264
Vice President Jeon Jae-yeol
as the potential third president.

810
00:59:24,391 --> 00:59:25,684
I look forward to seeing

811
00:59:26,310 --> 00:59:27,352
your wise decisions.

812
00:59:31,273 --> 00:59:32,858
Thank you, Mr. President.

813
00:59:32,941 --> 00:59:35,319
Before we vote on appointing

814
00:59:35,402 --> 00:59:37,988
Vice President Jeon Jae-yeol
as the next president

815
00:59:38,072 --> 00:59:41,200
does anyone have
any questions or objections?

816
00:59:45,120 --> 00:59:47,164
- If there aren't any...
- I object.

817
00:59:51,502 --> 00:59:55,047
Is your objection
regarding the appointment

818
00:59:55,130 --> 00:59:56,882
of the next president?

819
00:59:59,843 --> 01:00:01,303
Yes, that is correct.

820
01:00:02,012 --> 01:00:05,390
Vice President Jeon Jae-yeol
does not qualify to be the president.

821
01:00:05,474 --> 01:00:06,475
Because

822
01:00:08,852 --> 01:00:12,231
he did something he shouldn't have

823
01:00:15,609 --> 01:00:18,445
and his ex-girlfriend,
the Head of Audit, covered it up.

824
01:00:20,364 --> 01:00:22,908
What do you mean?
Do you have evidence?

825
01:00:23,242 --> 01:00:25,202
Of course, evidence is important.

826
01:00:26,620 --> 01:00:28,997
Hence, I invited someone

827
01:00:29,081 --> 01:00:31,542
who will witness everything
with her own words.

828
01:00:32,584 --> 01:00:34,962
Someone who knows
President Jeon Jae-yeol

829
01:00:35,337 --> 01:00:37,005
the best.

830
01:02:19,650 --> 01:02:22,569
FILING FOR LOVE

831
01:02:50,681 --> 01:02:53,517
About Ms. Park's report...
How much of it is true?

832
01:02:53,600 --> 01:02:55,310
Bring Joo In-a down at all costs.

833
01:02:55,394 --> 01:02:56,770
What trick are you pulling again?

834
01:02:57,229 --> 01:02:59,147
In-a, just hand in your resignation.

835
01:03:00,482 --> 01:03:02,567
Mr. Noh, is this article about you?

836
01:03:02,651 --> 01:03:03,652
That you're her lover?

837
01:03:03,735 --> 01:03:05,112
You're the one who told me

838
01:03:05,487 --> 01:03:07,990
to take a good look
at who's really falling apart.

839
01:03:08,740 --> 01:03:11,493
Ki-jun seems to be
the one who's falling apart.

840
01:03:11,827 --> 01:03:12,869
I'm not making any settlements.

841
01:03:12,953 --> 01:03:14,579
I'll protect you until the end.

842
01:03:15,956 --> 01:03:17,791
No matter what I say from now on

843
01:03:18,208 --> 01:03:20,043
it means that I love you.

844
01:03:33,056 --> 01:03:35,058
Subtitles by Eunsook Youn
and Jennifer Lim

